if the new feature—handling errors through retries—is covered. It looks like the Decoder MonadError handles errors in a library-specific way. I’ll need to consider if I should test this new logic, even if it branches from an existing implementation while still following the same base logic.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing decoder test coverage**\\n\\nI’m examining the coverage for failure paths in the traversal test, particularly with foldLeft and foldRight. There’s a possibility of adding a test for decoding attempts that fail, like `Show[Attempt[Int]].show(Attempt.failure(Err(\\\"missing payload\\\")))`, which might reveal a source bug. However, I'm thinking it’s better to create a separate test for the Decoder's Applicative composition using `mapN`. The existing decoder functionality supports sequential decoding, and I need to consider if there's a gap in testing functional features with `mapN`. It seems like just one new test might suffice!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Ensuring Scala 3 compilation**\\n\\nI need to make sure that the Scala 3 code compiles properly. I might need to check if I have the necessary imports, particularly for Monad, since I've already included Applicative. It seems like importing `cats.Monad` might be required, but I wonder if the existing `cats.implicits._` will suffice. It’s always a bit tricky ensuring every import is in place, but I’ll double-check to avoid any compilation issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_k3KzR3s0ENPBPFzNZoIKezXK|fc_0e2e18d9ae930c900169fc86d9c26c819591a4dabdcfa273db", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scodec/scodec-cats_3/1.2.0/src/test/scala/org_scodec/scodec_cats_3/Scodec_cats_3Test.scala", "edits": [{"oldText": "  @Test\n  def combinesDecodersForSemigroupOnlyResults(): Unit = {", "newText": "  @Test\n  def decoderErrorHandlingPreservesSuccessfulDecodesAndRetriesFallbackFromOriginalInput(): Unit = {\n    val decoderMonad: MonadError[Decoder, Err] = MonadError[Decoder, Err]\n    val source: BitVector = BitVector.fromValidHex(\"2a63\")\n    val expected: Attempt[DecodeResult[Int]] = Attempt.successful(DecodeResult(42, BitVector.fromValidHex(\"63\")))\n\n    val successfulPassThrough: Attempt[DecodeResult[Int]] = decoderMonad\n      .handleErrorWith(uint8)(_ => decoderMonad.pure(255))\n      .decode(source)\n    val failingAfterFirstByte: Decoder[Int] = decoderMonad.flatMap(uint8) { firstByte =>\n      decoderMonad.raiseError[Int](Err(s\"rejecting byte $firstByte\"))\n    }\n    val recoveredFromOriginalInput: Attempt[DecodeResult[Int]] = decoderMonad\n      .handleErrorWith(failingAfterFirstByte)(_ => uint8)\n      .decode(source)\n\n    assertThat(successfulPassThrough).isEqualTo(expected)\n    assertThat(recoveredFromOriginalInput).isEqualTo(expected)\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def combinesDecodersForSemigroupOnlyResults(): Unit = {"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3319, "output": 1400, "cacheRead": 27648, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32367, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778157257009, "responseId": "resp_0e2e18d9ae930c900169fc86c9a9c48195b574f1791847b168"}}
